title: SpaceX Reveals Details Of Next Generation Starlink Satellites
summary: SpaceX is set to the first batch of Starlink version 2 mini satellites from SLC-40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida on Monday.

title: SpaceX, NASA to launch international Crew-6 mission to Station
summary: SpaceX and NASA are ready to launch four people to the International Space Station (ISS), which will be their home for approximately six months. The Crew-6 astronauts are scheduled to liftoff onboard the Crew Dragon Endeavour atop a Falcon 9 rocket from Launch Complex 39A (LC-39A) at the Kennedy Space Center. T0 is set for Feb. 27 at 1:45 AM EST (6:45 UTC).

title: Replacement Soyuz arrives at space station
summary: An uncrewed Soyuz spacecraft launched to replace a damaged Soyuz arrived at the International Space Station Feb. 25.

title: Uncrewed Soyuz MS-23 “rescue” mission arrives at ISS
summary: The Russian space agency, Roscosmos, docked an uncrewed Soyuz spacecraft to the International Space Station (ISS) as part of a plan to replace the stricken Soyuz MS-22 vehicle. The MS-23 mission launched atop a Soyuz-2.1a rocket from Site 31/6 at the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan on Friday, Feb. 24, at 00:24 UTC. It docked without issue on Saturday.

title: First Image from SONY Star Sphere Satellite Released
summary: Sony has released the first test picture from their new Star Sphere satellite camera.
